    "summary": "I investigate electronic superstructures in Van der Waals materials, such as stacking domains in multilayer graphene (both twisted and others) as well as Charge Density Waves in Transition Metal Dichalcogenides, e.g. TaS2.\n\nThe main measurement tool for my research is a Low Energy Electron Microscope (LEEM), of which we are always trying to push the boundaries of what information can be extracted on the atomic and electronic structure of materials. \nI particularly enjoy a mix of challenges posed by the combination of computational data analysis, conversion of raw experimental data to physically meaningful data and the relating of microscopy data to new physical phenomena.",
